    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Natural depressions or courses in the earth's surface that are filled with water seasonally or for other reasons fluctuate between wet and dry, depending upon rainfall, snowmelt, or other factors.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
